  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wood-fired oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Rinse the mussels under cold water, discarding any broken shells.",
    "In a large bowl, mix together the coconut milk, ghee, cumin seeds, cayenne pepper, salt, cilantro, garlic, and ginger.",
    "Add the mussels to the bowl and toss to coat with the sauce.",
    "Transfer the mussels to the preheated wood-fired oven and bake for 10 minutes.",
    "Check the mussels for doneness and continue baking for another 5 minutes if needed.",
    "Remove the mussels from the oven and squeeze the lime juice over the top.",
    "Serve the mussels hot on a tagliere, garnished with additional cilantro if desired."
